The paper deals with super-resolution techniques for digital images, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new database for benchmarking these techniques, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of these techniques under various conditions, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or machine learning (cs.LG).
